==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whip-poor-will
<hw>Whip"-poor-will`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>An American bird (<spn>Antrostomus vociferus</spn>) allied to the
nighthawk and goatsucker; -- so called in imitation of the peculiar
notes which it utters in the evening.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>whippowil</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whipsaw</ent>⟦br⟧
